  "prompt": "How can I watch YouTube videos on a VLC media player?",
  "response": "To watch YouTube videos on VLC media player, follow these steps:\n\n1. Update VLC to the latest version (recommended)\n\n2. Open VLC media player\n\n3. Go to Media > Open Network Stream (or press Ctrl+N)\n\n4. Copy the YouTube video URL you want to watch\n\n5. Paste the URL into the network stream window\n\n6. Click \"Play\" or press Enter\n\nAlternatively, you can:\n\n1. Use the \"YouTube\" plugin/extension within VLC\n2. Use online converters to get direct video stream links\n3. Use third-party software like youtube-dl (command-line tool)\n\nNote: YouTube may periodically change its systems, which can temporarily affect VLC's ability to play videos directly. In such cases, you might need to update VLC or try alternative methods.\n\nAdditional tip: Some people prefer using the official YouTube website or app for the best viewing experience and up-to-date features.",
